cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on improving the QoS of mobile users by placing drone base stations in the cellular network. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the optimization problem of placing drone base stations to minimize the total average latency ratio of mobile users. This involves information theory concepts such as channel capacity and latency. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The placement of drone base stations involves controlling the network to improve QoS. This falls under the domain of systems and control. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The LEAP algorithm designed to solve the DBS placement problem efficiently involves optimization techniques that are commonly used in artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The placement of drone base stations involves coordinating multiple agents (i.e., the DBSs) to improve the overall performance of the network. This falls under the domain of multiagent systems.
